  "summary": "Added hidden-bisect rowchunk tracing support and used it to compare derived rows4/5/6 c3 full-attention context traces. L4 decode-step probes show native full grouping, rowchunk2, and per-row full-attention all have raw attn_context parity vs independent c1. At the L40 trace window around generated index 11, native full grouping is already red at layer7 attn_input_pre_qkv before attn_context, so the observed context drift is inherited rather than proving the context kernel is the first faulty stage. Rowchunk2 trace support itself is green at L4; L40 rowchunk2 hidden-bisect remains red in this short hidden trace and is retained-blocked, so no performance/retained claim is made.",
